                    <BLOCKQUOTE><TABLE border="1"><TBODY><TR><TD><BLOCKQUOTE><DIV><IMG src="http://cache.LEGO.com/images/forums/en-US/icon-quote.gif" /> <STRONG>talmid wrote:</STRONG></DIV><DIV class="quoteTable"><BLOCKQUOTE><DIV>Cool!<BR />___<BR />_/&amp;nbsp; 0 /\/ /\/ /-\<BR /> </DIV></BLOCKQUOTE><BR />I'm not sure what Thingguy had in mind, but multiple stories would be fun! <BR /><BR /><BR /><BR /><BR /><BR /><BR /><BR />About your previous post, I really hope your computer gets fixed!  And about who's going to write the next chapter....<BR /><BR /><BR /><BR /><BR /><BR /><BR /><BR />...right now Luke is inactive, and thinking of Luke, I need to bump Skyward again for him.&amp;nbsp; Legoboy is I think not writing, Ninjago Builders I think wants to write, Ethan.... is he writing?&amp;nbsp; I can't remember if Firelash is writing, I'm too lazy to check. <BR /><BR /><BR /><BR /> </DIV></BLOCKQUOTE><BR />No need! For I can now post a chapter!!! At least, I'm 70% sure I can... but I'll give it a whack if nobody else is already working on one! I was thinking... well I guess I should do jammers.<BR /><BR /><BR /><BR /><BR /><BR /><BR /><BR />JAMMERS ON! KOTOS ONLY!!!<BR /><BR /><BR /><BR />I was thinking I would switch to Jonna's view, riding across the lost plains, going on and on about how her father was going to listen to her after this and let her learn how to use a sword. And chatting away with Squeaky. So, if everyone else is okey-dokey with it, could I take this chapter? At least, I'll try it, but I'm pretty sure I'll be able to get past the limit.<BR /><BR /><BR /><BR />JAMMERS OFF!!!<BR /><BR /><BR /><BR />___<BR /><BR /><BR /><BR />_/  0 /\/ /\/ /-\ <BR />JAMMERS ON KOTOS ONLY!!!!!!<BR /><BR />Sounds good, but I don't want to sound like a hypocrite.&nbsp; I told EthanWS we should stay with the perspective of the Knights for now, and then if went ahead and went with what you're saying I'd become a mean hypocritical Thomas Jefferson.  (Note: I actually really